	(110,2,'2013-05-28 04:21:44','2013-05-28 04:21:44','Scotty is a software engineer for the <a href=\"http://nytimes.com\">New York Times</a> by day, and lead guitarist for <strong><a href=\"http://www.goodbyepicasso.com\">Goodbye Picasso</a></strong> on the weekends. His favorite food is tacos.\r\n\r\nAllie is a political organizer who heads up <strong><a href=\"http://www.nyclass.org\">NYCLASS</a></strong>, an animal protection organization working on banning horse carriages and other animal rights issues in NYC. Her favorite food is veggie dogs.\r\n\r\nWilla is our adopted cat from <strong><a href=\"http://www.nycacc.org\">NYC Animal Care and Control</a></strong>.\r\n\r\nWe love going to concerts, Peacefood Cafe on the Upper West Side, watching Bill Maher on DVR on Sunday afternoons, reading about NYC history, FSU football and traveling to Mexico.','About Us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2015-01-11 02:58:50','2015-01-11 02:58:50','',0,'http://scottyandallie.com/?page_id=110',2,'page','',0),
	(108,2,'2013-10-21 03:27:48','2013-10-21 03:27:48','<a href=\"http://fullmooncentral.com/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-121 aligncenter\" alt=\"indx_logo2bed1210\" src=\"http://scottyandallie.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/indx_logo2bed1210-300x146.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"146\" /></a>\n\nWe are SO EXCITED. Our wedding weekend will be Friday, September 19th through  Sunday, September 21st of 2014. (Lots of people have 22 month long engagements....) This date is special to us because it\'s our 10 year anniversary.\n\nThe location is <a href=\"http://www.fullmoonresort.com/\">Full Moon Resort</a> in Big Indian, NY.\n\nIt\'s going to be an awesome three day festival of family, friends, music, nature and love. Full Moon Resort is 20 minutes from Woodstock. It\'s on the top of a mountain so there\'s no cell phone service.\n\nMore details coming. Save the date!\n\n-Allie &amp; Scott','We have a date and a venue!','','inherit','open','open','','107-autosave','','','2013-10-21 03:27:48','2013-10-21 03:27:48','',107,'http://scottyandallie.com/2013/05/20/107-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),
	(167,3,'2014-06-03 02:31:34','2014-06-03 02:31:34','Scotty is a software engineer for the <a href=\"http://nytimes.com\">New York Times</a> by day, and lead guitarist for <a href=\"http://www.goodbyepicasso.com\">Goodbye Picasso</a> by night.\n\nAllie is a political organizer who heads up <a href=\"http://www.nyclass.org\">NYCLASS</a>, an animal protection organization working to ban horse carriages in NYC.\n\nWilla is our adopted cat from <a href=\"http://www.nycacc.org\">NYC Animal Care and Control</a>.\n\nWe love going to concerts, Peacefood Cafe on the Upper West Side, watching Bill Maher on DVR on Sunday afternoons, and traveling to Mexico.','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','110-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-03 02:31:34','2014-06-03 02:31:34','',110,'http://scottyandallie.com/2014/06/03/110-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(195,3,'2014-08-07 03:22:11','2014-08-07 03:22:11','<strong>1. What time should I arrive? Where am I going?</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can start checking into your room at Full Moon at the main area (Valley View house) starting at 3PM on Friday, June 5. We will be vibing at Valley View from 3-6PM with snacks &amp; music. Then the first official event is the BBQ at 7PM.\r\n\r\nThe weekend itinerary is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://scottyandallie.com/itinerary/\">here</a></span>. Directions <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://scottyandallie.com/driving-directions/\">here</a></span>. Be sure to give yourself at least 3 hours to drive from NY/NJ -- there is a ton of traffic on Fridays.\r\n\r\nFor folks staying off-site at Alpine Inn, you can check in as early as 1PM. After you checkin at Alpine, please come join us at Full Moon.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. What should I bring? What should I wear?</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Country chic attire for Friday\'s 7PM BBQ and Yacht Rock party. Think sundress for women and button down shirt for men, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Formal attire for Saturday\'s 5PM wedding ceremony and reception. Suit or tux for men, and cocktail dress or gown for women.</li>\r\n	<li>Swimsuit, flip flops and beach towel for the pool.</li>\r\n	<li>Jacket or sweater - it can get cold at night</li>\r\n	<li>Bathrobe/slippers <i>(some guest rooms have shared baths or hall baths)</i></li>\r\n	<li>Hairdryer</li>\r\n	<li>Flashlight</li>\r\n	<li>Umbrella</li>\r\n	<li>Cash for the bar at the after-parties on Friday &amp; Saturday nights -- the bar does not take credit cards and there is no ATM for 20 miles.</li>\r\n	<li>Musical instruments, if you\'d like to play around the campfire or jam at the after parties</li>\r\n	<li>If you\'d like to explore hiking trails, bring boots or sneakers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>3. What does Full Moon provide for guests?</strong>\r\n\r\nFull Moon is a rustic lodging facility, not a hotel, but it\'s quaint, clean and provides:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bath towels &amp; bed linens</li>\r\n	<li>Shampoo, conditioner, soap</li>\r\n	<li>Ice</li>\r\n	<li>Complimentary teas and coffee at Valley View from the time breakfast is served until the last meal of the day is served</li>\r\n	<li>Front desk has emergency and basic medical equipment (bandaids, tylenol, etc). Closest pharmacy is approximately 20 minutes from Full Moon.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHousekeeping services are not provided during the course of the stay. Extra towels may be obtained from the front desk as needed.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>4. What\'s the weather like?</strong>\r\n\r\nNestled in the Catskill Mountains, it will be in the 70\'s - 80\'s F.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Is there cell phone reception?</strong>\r\n\r\nThere is no cell phone reception at Full Moon Resort or in the forest preserve but <strong><em>there is free WiFi so you can still send and receive texts and emails</em></strong>. Also, complimentary landline phone service is available at all times at Valley View.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Can I bring my own alcohol?</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can bring your own cooler and alcohol for use in your room.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>7. How can guests be reached at Full Moon?</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease call the front desk at Full Moon at (845) 254 - 5117.\r\n\r\n<strong>8. </strong><strong>My question isn\'t here.</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease email allie@scottyandallie.com or call us: Allie 908-370-2689 and Scotty 646-715-7347.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','publish','closed','closed','','faq','','','2015-05-24 18:10:42','2015-05-24 18:10:42','',0,'http://scottyandallie.com/?page_id=195',0,'page','',0),
