	(223,2,'2015-01-11 03:10:13','2015-01-11 03:10:13','Scotty is a software engineer for the <a href=\"http://nytimes.com\">New York Times</a> by day, and lead guitarist for <strong><a href=\"http://www.goodbyepicasso.com\">Goodbye Picasso</a></strong> on the weekends. His favorite food is tacos.\r\n\r\nAllie is a political organizer who heads up <strong><a href=\"http://www.nyclass.org\">NYCLASS</a></strong>, an animal protection organization working on banning horse carriages and other animal rights issues in NYC. Her favorite food is veggie dogs.\r\n\r\nWilla is our adopted cat from <strong><a href=\"http://www.nycacc.org\">NYC Animal Care and Control</a></strong>.\r\n\r\nWe love going to concerts, Peacefood Cafe on the Upper West Side, watching Bill Maher on DVR on Sunday afternoons, reading about NYC history, FSU football and traveling to Mexico.','About Us','','inherit','open','closed','','110-autosave-v1','','','2015-01-11 03:10:13','2015-01-11 03:10:13','',110,'http://scottyandallie.com/2015/01/11/110-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(260,2,'2015-05-22 13:06:32','2015-05-22 13:06:32','<strong>PLEASE NOTE:</strong> <em>There is a music festival happening the same weekend as the wedding -- please give yourself extra time to get there.</em>\n\n<strong>ADDRESS:</strong> Full Moon Resort, 12 Valley View Road, Big Indian, NY 12410\n\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (845) 254-5117 www.fullmoonresort.com\n\n<strong>From the Albany area and Points North (~1.75hrs): </strong>Take New York State Thruway (87) South towards New York City. Get off at Exit 19, Kingston. Take Route 28 West (toward Pine Hill.) Travel approximately 30 miles on Route 28 West to Big Indian/Oliverea. Turn left onto County Route 47 (just after a brown sign on Route 28 which says “Oliverea 3 miles”). Proceed 5 miles on Route 47. Full Moon is on the right. You will see signs. Pull down the Full Moon driveway, parking areas should be clearly designated. If you see the entrance for Pine Hill, on your left, you have gone too far.\n\n<strong>From the New York City area and Points South (~2.5hrs):</strong> Take the New York State Thruway (87) North to Exit 19 (Kingston). Take Route 28 West (toward Pine Hill.) Travel approximately 30 miles on Route 28 West to Big Indian/Oliverea. Turn left onto County Route 47 (just after a brown sign on Route 28 which says “Oliverea 3 miles”). Proceed 5 miles on Route 47. Full Moon is on the right. You will see signs. Pull down the Full Moon driveway, parking areas should be clearly designated. If you see the entrance for Pine Hill, on your left, you have gone too far.\n\n<strong>From Buffalo/Rochester area and Points North West (~4.5hrs-Roch / </strong><strong>5.5hrs-Buff):</strong> Take the New York State Thruway (I-90) East to Exit 39 (Syracuse). Take I-81 South (toward Binghamton.) Travel approximately 75 miles on I-81 South and, near Binghamton, take NY-17E toward New York. Travel approximately 47 miles on NY-17E to Exit 90; RT-30 N (toward Downsville). Merge quickly onto NY-30 / CR-17 / OLD RT-17 (slight Right). Continue to follow NY-30 for about 38 miles (some curves and turns). Turn Right on NY-28 and travel for approximately 16 miles. You will pass Peekamoose Restaurant (on your right), go over a bridge and see a statue of an Indian on your right as you near the resort. After you pass the Indian statue take a sharp right onto County Route 47. Proceed 5 miles on Route 47. Full Moon is on the right. You will see signs. Pull down the Full Moon driveway, parking areas should be clearly designated.\n\n<strong>From the Boston area and Points North East (~4hrs):</strong> Take Mass Pike West (I-90). Travel approximately 150 miles and merge onto New York State Thruway West (I-87). After about 7miles, merge onto I-87 South towards New York City. Get off at Exit 19, Kingston. Take Route 28 West (toward Pine Hill.) Travel approximately 30 miles on Route 28 West to Big Indian/Oliverea. Turn left onto County Route 47 (just after a brown sign on Route 28 which says “Oliverea 3 miles”). Proceed 5 miles on Route 47. Full Moon is on the right. You will see signs. Pull down the Full Moon driveway, parking areas should be clearly designated. If you see the entrance for Pine Hill, on your left, you have gone too far.','Driving Directions','','inherit','open','closed','','258-autosave-v1','','','2015-05-22 13:06:32','2015-05-22 13:06:32','',258,'http://scottyandallie.com/2015/02/07/258-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
